info.description:
Complete API collection for WorkPulse workforce productivity tracking platform.

WebSocket Testing:
- Connect to: ws://localhost:3000/cable?token={{token}}
- Subscribe to OrganizationChannel: {"command":"subscribe","identifier":"{\"channel\":\"OrganizationChannel\"}"}
- Subscribe to UserChannel: {"command":"subscribe","identifier":"{\"channel\":\"UserChannel\"}"}

Note: WebSocket requests must be created separately in Postman (New > WebSocket Request). The identifier field must be a JSON string, not an object.

request.description:
Get batch activity data for a session. Returns activity data in the same format as POST batch_activity, including screenshots.

**Response (200 OK):**
```json
{
  "sessionId": 762,
  "timestamp": "2026-02-16T12:55:00Z",
  "totalMinutes": 10,
  "aggregatedData": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "fullTimestamp": "2026-02-16T10:58:57.353Z",
      "activeSeconds": 49,
      "idleSeconds": 10,
      "keyboardEvents": 1,
      "mouseEvents": 39,
      "activeWindowTitle": "VS Code",
      "windowTitles": { "VS Code": 60 }
    }
  ],
  "hourlyActivity": [
    {
      "hour": "10:00",
      "activeSeconds": 49,
      "idleSeconds": 10,
      "productivity_percentage": 83.1,
      "topApp": "VS Code"
    }
  ],
  "summary": {
    "userId": "user@example.com",
    "totalActiveSeconds": 354,
    "totalIdleSeconds": 245,
    "totalKeyboardEvents": 1,
    "totalMouseEvents": 322,
    "screenshots": [
      {
        "id": 1,
        "timestamp": "2026-02-16T10:58:57.353Z",
        "sessionId": 762,
        "userId": 1
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

Send batch activity data for a session. The session ID can be provided in the URL path or in the request body as `sessionId`.

**Request Body Formats:**
1. **Summary only (minimal):**
```json
{
  "sessionId": 123,
  "timestamp": "2026-02-16T12:55:00.149Z",
  "totalMinutes": 1,
  "summary": {
    "userId": "user@example.com",
    "totalActiveSeconds": 22,
    "totalIdleSeconds": 37,
    "totalKeyboardEvents": 0,
    "totalMouseEvents": 21
  }
}
```

2. **With screenshots (top-level or in summary):**
```json
{
  "sessionId": 123,
  "timestamp": "2026-02-16T12:55:00.149Z",
  "totalMinutes": 1,
  "screenshots": [
    {
      "id": "ss1",
      "timestamp": "2026-02-16T12:55:00.149Z"
    }
  ],
  "summary": {
    "userId": "user@example.com",
    "totalActiveSeconds": 22,
    "totalIdleSeconds": 37
  }
}
```

3. **With aggregatedData (full):**
```json
{
  "sessionId": 123,
  "timestamp": "2026-02-16T12:55:00.149Z",
  "totalMinutes": 1,
  "aggregatedData": [
    {
      "fullTimestamp": "2026-02-16T10:58:57.353Z",
      "activeSeconds": 49,
      "idleSeconds": 10,
      "keyboardEvents": 1,
      "mouseEvents": 39,
      "activeWindowTitle": "VS Code",
      "windowTitles": {
        "VS Code": 60
      }
    }
  ],
  "summary": {
    "totalActiveSeconds": 22,
    "totalIdleSeconds": 37
  }
}
```

**Response (201 Created):**
```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "message": "Batch activity data saved",
  "minutes_saved": 1,
  "session_id": 123,
  "session": {
    "id": 123,
    "user_id": 1,
    "start_time": "2026-02-16T12:00:00Z",
    "end_time": null,
    "last_activity_at": "2026-02-16T12:55:00Z",
    "total_active_seconds": 22,
    "total_idle_seconds": 37,
    "status": "active"
  }
}
```

